  "prompt": "What is a boy/girl called when he/she is 1-6 years old, 6-11years old, 11-14 years old, and 14-18 years old?",
  "response": "The terms used to describe children and adolescents at different ages can vary somewhat, but generally, the following classifications are commonly used:\n\n1. **1-6 years old**: This age range is typically referred to as \"early childhood.\" Children in this age group are often called \"toddlers\" (especially around ages 1-3) and \"preschoolers\" (around ages 3-5), transitioning to \"young children\" or \"school-aged children\" as they approach age 6.\n\n2. **6-11 years old**: This period is commonly known as \"middle childhood.\" Children in this age group are often referred to as \"school-aged children\" or simply \"children.\"\n\n3. **11-14 years old**: This age range is typically referred to as \"early adolescence\" or \"pre-adolescence.\" Individuals in this group are often called \"preteens\" or \"tweens.\"\n\n4. **14-18 years old**: This period is commonly known as \"adolescence.\" Individuals in this age group are often referred to as \"teenagers\" or \"teens.\"\n\nThese terms help to categorize developmental stages and provide a framework for understanding the physical, emotional, and social changes that occur during these periods.",
